  "prompt": "Who wrote the 2nd amendment?",
  "response": "The Second Amendment to the United States Constitution was written by James Madison, who is often referred to as the \"Father of the Constitution.\" Madison introduced the Bill of Rights, which includes the first ten amendments to the Constitution, during the first session of the United States Congress in **1789**. \n\nThe text of the Second Amendment reads:  \n\"A well-regulated Militia, being necessary to the security of a free State, the right of the people to keep and bear Arms, shall not be infringed.\"\n\nThe amendment was influenced by historical precedents, such as the English Bill of Rights of 1689 and the colonial experience with militias, as well as the desire to ensure individual and collective defense in the newly formed United States. It was ratified and became part of the Constitution on **December 15, 1791**.",
